node.text: Hello, welcome back to Home Movies. Today it’s a GRILLED FISH FOR YOU! Not just the fish, a whole dinner to make with it, including by not limited to this summers hottest accessory: ORZO. Truly hope that idea is as thrilling for you as it is for me. Tune in, like, subscribe, etc. 📽 @dannyhurwitz @mattmaltese.mov

node.text: Home Movies! PIE 101. There are a million ways to make a pie, this is one. While there’s intel on the crust, filling, rolling, baking and slicing, the true moral of the story here is that I believe there is a direct correlation between a pies imperfections and it’s deliciousness. Simple math, I don’t make the rules, etc. link in bio to watch 🥧 🎬 @dannyhurwitz @mattmaltese.mov

node.text: In today’s newsletter I answer an important question about green beans, a criminally underrated and comically abundant vegetable. Plus: what’s the best month to move to New York and what’s the difference between cast iron and stainless steel? 🌵First slide recipe for blanched beans with scallion and soy available in the inbox today- new favorite ceramic plate by @chefjennydorsey because what can’t she do? (charred beans with anchovy’d walnuts & harissa braised beans with tomato both from Nothing Fancy, those photos by @graydonherriott props @kalen_k_ 👨‍👩‍👧‍👧💕)

node.text: Worshiping vegetables the best way we know how 🌞 🌾🥕7/31, a very special dinner to support the most special @starroutefarm in their pursuit in pivoting to full-time food access farming. Cooking alongside @jointventurenyc @starroutefarm next to a gorgeous pond, with a beautiful fire, with lovely wines from @wildcommonwine and the best vodka from @good.vodka 🍷🍸If you can’t make it, please consider a $30 donation (listed under “community plate” on the eventbrite page) to support their work. TICKET LINK IN BIO, SPOTS ARE LIMITED, MAGIC WILL BE MADE, VIBES WILL BE GOOD! We hope to see you there 🌻

node.text: Home Movies Tuesday! Some fun BTS: the day we shot this it never stopped raining, it was dark as hell all day, we couldn’t grill so I did this stovetop, it was before I got an AC in my apt, it was hot as hell, I was in a terrible mood, but WOW we all agreed this chicken was WORTH EVERY PAINFUL SECOND! We suffer for our art! Thanks to everyone on set who didn’t quit this day!!! Please enjoy! 📽 @davidcho @dannyhurwitz with edits by @curtiswhitear

node.text: This week on Home Movies, my favorite thing for all-day eating: slow-cooked tuna with white beans (and celery salad, because tuna without celery is simply no tuna at all). The tuna is fresh, the beans come from a can, and you can re-use the oil for many things, like simmering said beans and making a superlative aioli/mayo. What a gorgeous love story! Link in bio to watch.

node.text: WELCOME BACK TO HOME MOVIES. Three summer salads! Make them, eat them, love them. Plus: yes, I moved! And while it’s a work in progress, I now have a regular sized fridge and am feeling so blessed. No official home tour yet, those scare me, but I uh, did my best (“here’s where I keep some stuff, and also my bouquet of dill”). Link to watch 🔝 📽 @dannyhurwitz
